@startuml
title Browser Auth Bundle Boundary (After)
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontColor #000000
skinparam ArrowColor #000000
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName Consolas

actor "Browser User" as User #DCEBFA
component "Client Component\n(header/login/reset-password)" as Client #DCFCE7
component "lib/auth/athena-browser-auth.ts\n(browser proxy)" as BrowserAuth #DCFCE7
component "Route Handler\n/api/auth/[action]" as AuthApiRoute #DBEAFE
component "utils/athena/auth-client.ts\nimport \"server-only\"" as ServerAuthFactory #E0E7FF
component "@xylex-group/athena dist/index.js\n(server runtime only)" as AthenaSdk #E0E7FF
component "Node-only deps\npg, fs/promises, net, tls, util/types" as NodeDeps #BFDBFE

User --> Client : interacts with auth UI
Client --> BrowserAuth : call auth methods
BrowserAuth --> AuthApiRoute : POST /api/auth/{action}\ncredentials include
AuthApiRoute --> ServerAuthFactory : createAthenaAuthClient({ fetch })
ServerAuthFactory --> AthenaSdk : server-side import
AthenaSdk --> NodeDeps : resolved on server only

note right of BrowserAuth
No direct import of @xylex-group/athena
in the browser bundle.
Session token remains client-managed
and auth calls stay proxied through Next API.
end note
@enduml
